Flavor Text: You think this is funny, don't you?
Unassuming but determined pests.
One in a krillion.
Small, frail, but ever so useful.
Nonthreatening, if you leave it be.
Just a little guy.
What purpose could it serve?
Small, frail, and pathetic... for now.
A friend-shaped regenerator.
Seemingly lazy, but ever watchful.
Quite a... shocking specimen.
Tiny, scuttling, but resilient stature.
Young, ambitious, and scared.
A pest alone, but devastating in swarm.
A swift, slippery hunter.
A slight incarnation of terror.
Curious...
Blind, but seemingly omnipresent.
Vicious pack-hunters of the rivers.
An ornery, ever-annoying rodent.
A scrappy little gatherer.
No less conniving in incubation.
It makes its own electrical surges.
Resoundingly pointless, with little use.
Elusive, but not very menacing.
Just a touch could be deadly.
It is trying to evade death at any cost.
A horrid stench to keep predators away.
Meek and feeble, yes, but ever so useful.
An odd, almost unnatural behavior.
A lowly, but ever noble creature.
A minor problem... if not ignored.
A bountiful pit of hares.
An ambitious predator, needing only time.
Weak alone, but overwhelming in force.
Always lethal, the caustic adder.
An industrious creature.
Interesting...
A fiercely loyal companion.
The force of its bite is inescapable.
Sharpens its' teeth on scounged bones.
Hearty of form, but flighty of nature.
Where there is one, another is not far.
A skittish, but cunning predator.
Strange...
A violently efficient bird of prey.
Drawing the eyes of hungry beasts.
A frail turtle, protected by its shell.
An ingenious escape artist.
Oddly sadistic, this venerable beast.
Tragic royalty, destined to crumble.
Horribly clever, this blight of a bird is.
Stalwart in the face of adversity.
Little can stop this rampaging brute.
A proud and ferocious contender.
A massive stomach for a big appetite.
A horrifyingly efficient pest.
Truly unrelenting, this terrifying canine.
Go fish.
Its form speaks enough of its efficacy.
It's hard to call it cowardly...
The hard work of an industrious beast.
Does your mouth not water at the sight?
Resourceful, weak, but endearing.
A minor, meddlesome terror.
Its incessant buzz brought insanity.
A meager but dangerous scavenger.
Determined to inflict its aggression.
A venerable leader, emboldening others.
Always inevitable, emerging from death.
Brittle, if you can survive its bite.
A vicious beast, bathed in blood.
A horrid tyrant upon the skies.
A true sacrifice, despite all the blood.
It may not die, but it does feel the pain.
Picking fights with everything.
A curious gadget in the shape of a beast.
Regal, royal, and a mother of pests.
An ancient, voracious specimen.
A collector of trinkets and trash alike.
Defenseless, but well-stocked.
A sanguine beast, doused in blood.
Expectedly slippery. Surprisingly strong.
A horrific bird with a peculiar diet.
A towering and ever-powerful beast.
An immortal, persistent nuisance.
Uninspiring, but charming despite it all.
Vicious in looks, but frail in nature.
A perfect incarnation of terror.
An unyielding, ultimate defense.
Amalgam is all.
Left abandoned, cursed, and hungry.
It just wants love.
A fearsome, hellacious creature.
It will always return.
A prudent rat bearing trinkets.
A ravenous beast with insatiable hunger.
Whalers gone mad at the mere sight.
This level of brutality needs no words.
Always different, ever-changing.

Sigils: Rabbit Hole, Prism Gem, Battery Bearer, Bone Digger
Flavor Text: "Ah, young one! A pleasure to see you!"
"Careful, now. Use me wisely."
"Yep, it's me. Nice topdeck."
"You didn't need that card, right?"
"You play. I fish."
"Yet another turn of the skinning knife..."
"Your deck's a lil' lel, not gonna lie."
"'Tis a game o' chance! HEEEE-HAAW!!"
"I suppose it was only a matter of time."
"Salutations. A lucky draw."
A little spirit, happy to help.
A critter, wandering burial grounds.
A frail and spooky mass of bones.
Frozen in time, waiting for freedom.
They never stay dead for long.
A spooky visage in wood.
Willing to dig what needs to be dug.
He'll leave the bones for you to take.
A small, but honorable commemoration.
Rather happy, despite the crying.
Flings itself around the room, hazardly.
It is on the verge of burning out.
A once proud mage, left to rot.
A pirate in life, a pirate in death.
A bringer of illness, a siphon of life.
Naught but a corpse, left to rot.
The puppet becomes the puppeteer.
A corpse left rotten and deformed.
They just want to find their own grave.
Raves in taverns about lost sailors.
A good captain stops ships from sinking.
A bringer of death and renderer of flesh.
Always looming in the background.
An apt reflection of those around it.
Their numbers grow with their infection.
Still training to raise the dead properly.
Even the lowliest of spirits have use.
Overcome with a strain of disease.
Grotesque boils, ready to burst.
Sometimes, one little shovel isn't enough.
Banishing his kind.
Sewn together, friends forever.
Fully staffed and ready to plunder.
Nothing you do shall go unpunished.
His broken body sways in the breeze.

Sigils: Made of Stone, Night of the Living Dead
Flavor Text: A monument to the dearly departed.
A bloodsucking prowler of the night.
Traps an evil on the verge of escape.
Forced to harvest, as long as it stands.
They lived together, they died together.
An ancient cannibalistic spirit.
A spiteful visage of what once was.
Some are forced to scavenge the graves.
A corpse within a corpse.
Remains of a spirit, quick to expand.

Sigils: Made of Stone, Guardian, Mighty Leap
Flavor Text: Protecting the mausoleum, by force.
They search for knowledge beyond life.

Sigils: Burrower, Sharp Quills, Made of Stone, Bastion
Flavor Text: An invisible wall blocks the way.
Wherever they travel, death follows.
A common vessel for spirits.
A legionnaire in life, a soldier beyond.
Ever loyal, even beyond the grave.
The deceased won't resist much longer.
Bringing forth the rewards of each kill.
A persistent lie can be powerful.
Ever emboldening their undead horde.
Isn't nature beautiful?
What horrors lay inside its abject gut?
A monstrous force of ivory.
An infernal and sadistic creature.
Locked away, and for good reason.
That one seems happier in death.
Despite everything, the labor continues.
Boo!
An incorporeal menace.
A tool that's lived for a century.
An inescapable harbinger of death.
An unfortunate pile of meat and thought.
A scavenger of fresh blood.
Forever regrowing its own tissue.
An ever-imposing wall of meat.
Contains naught but secrets and fear.
The last wisp of a life snuffed out.
Has an affinity for all things brittle.
An inseperable pair, fit for a king.
Its companions won't leave them so soon.
Consuming whatever carrion it can find.
A monster in life, a monster in death.
Guardians of unknowable depths.
A venerable commander, more so in death.
Cobbled together from skin and bone.
Bones rattle in the night.
Prankish and playful, but oh so spiteful.
A conglomeration of tortured souls.
Poor creature... how it has suffered.
A mass of marrow and carrion.
This is a rather... interesting boon.
A shame no one was there to save them.
A stalwart spirit sharpshooter.
A little investment goes a long way.
Not all there, but carries a boon.
Words cannot describe this... creature.
Back from the grave, if only briefly.
Working the graveyard shift, together.
A frenzied hoard, seeking vengeance.
Sworn to protect, even from beyond.
Its labyrinth became its tomb.
Striking fear into all who see him.
The spite of a thousand bones, at once.

Sigils: Touch of Death, Bell Ringer, Haunter
Flavor Text: Your time is up.
Always in need of bloody sacrifice.
"Dude! Maybe turn up the heat a little?"
"P-Please don't play me..."
"I git t'live out me dream as a card!"
"Oh cool, it's me. Great."
"Craft your vision."
"Piracy is stealing! I love stealing!"
"From dust I am born, to dust I succumb."
"Wow, great draw!"
"Allow me to finish our calling."
"Cower! It is now the Witching Hour!"
Strong springs for jumping into action.
Transfers power, but not much else.
Shoots anything that gets close.
It's odd for rust to smell this bad.
The most basic in function and form.
Loading others with extreme explosives.
Your damage request has been denied.
Cold, but not calculating.
Full of energy that it cannot use.
What could it be hiding from you?
Well-meaning, but notoriously pushy.
A surprisingly helpful piece of tech.
On the move, searching for something.
Universally reviled, but always on time.
Also useful for producing glue.
Just barely able to make a connection.
An old model, but nonetheless effective.
The buzz of its flight is irritating.
It might be feeling generous.
A... curious bot indeed.
All bones obtained legally.*
Good play. Unfortunately...
Making renewable energy, with no waste.
Heavy and sluggish, but extremely solid.
Protective of what fuels them.
Protecting others better than itself.
Easy to aim, easy to shoot.
Its irritating screeches are unbearable.
An ornery little tin can.
Even blood contains iron.
Now you're playing with power.
A frail and spooky mass of scrap metal.
A bump could set it off.
Even in battle, the line does not stop.
It could blow at any moment...
Surprisingly sturdy, given its size.
We couldn't fit a fourth strike.
Sometimes they need a little extra juice.
Emeralds are great for data tracking.
Rubies make for great energy conductors.
Sapphires empower calculations.
It cannot handle its own energy.
Full of neurotoxins.
It's just happy to be here.
A vicious and twisted metal construct.
For complete and proper disposal.
A scuttling little worker machine.
Even works against explosives.
Keep their wires from getting tangled.
Can this be any more straightforward?
A vicious and protective bucket of bolts.
Works deep, even deeper than the Dredger.
Built for one singular function.
A violent bot of claws and bullets.
A metallic blight upon the skies.
Push your luck. What could go wrong?
Springloaded for causing problems.
The best offense is a good defense.
Once a fighter, always a fighter.
Reconfigures itself to suit its mood.
Twice the guns, twice the power.
Just one was never enough.
Sees all it can, where it can.
Makes its routine virus scan.
Nothing gets through without permission.
Surprisingly clean, as no one uses him.
The Cube.
An intelligence dedicated to sorting files.
An ultra high-power model.
Prowls factories searching intruders.
This is ducky, the big one.
You can't hold it back forever.
It's not magic, it just needs extra juice.
Best not let it die.
An inefficient use of power, at best.
Efficiency demands motion.
Provides a violent shock to the system.

Sigils: Hearty Offering, Life Donor, Convalesce, Sprinter
Flavor Text: Blood is a resource and commodity.
Takes problems into its own hands.
Gathers up scrap through brute force.
It uses... I dunno, quantum mechanics?
Clunky, inefficient, and reeks of fumes.
Shoots on command, without hesitation.
Adapts and reforms as needed.
Frog. Frog. Frog. Frog.
Statistically very powerful for its cost.
Infinite power at your fingertips.
A true beast, replicated by machinery.
The eternal android, unyielding by design.
Infinite power, itty bitty circuit space.
Has got quite the portfolio.
One photo to capture your last moment.
The strongest springs.
A bombshell, through and through.
Its internal clock is set to high noon.
A perfect weapon of mass destruction.
The solution/cause to all your problems.
Together, we are might!
"Oi, lookit. I'm somefin' uv a card."
"I suppose your deck is adequate."
"Doesn't matter. I'll just make it again."
"WE ARE-- I am... a good card."
"The true beasts are no more."
"I have a 1 in 36 chance of being meta!"
"Oh, and employee? You're Fired."
"Bolt Van Tankski reporting for duty."
"I've got it all, and then some!"
A conduit for magicks of the body.
A conduit for magicks of the soul.
A conduit for magicks of the mind.
A powerful conduit for all magicks.
Constantly losing their own research.
A new learner of magicks.
Some magicks simply must be stopped.
A pure reflection of one's own flaws.
Adept at casting spells from a distance.
Has time to reconsider their study field.
A well-known incantation.
They see all, as it is bare before them.
An immaculate construct of perfect mox.
"Lemme give that a new coat of paint!"
Recklessly practices transmutation.
A small agent of small magicks.
Saddening, artistic talent put to war.
They are powered directly by gems.
A hardy construct fueled by mox.
A new learner of the body's magicks.
Just loves to push people around.
They collect magickal remnants.
A faithful provider of their own body.
Can push themselves beyond their limits.
Wells of power sleep in fragments.
Magic is the heart of nature.
Here to welcome the new generation.
Fractured and maddened by the unknown.
Barely able to copy inscriptions.
Magick brought them to life.

Sigils: Green Gem, Green Gem, Fragment Hoard
Flavor Text: A formation high in magickal power.

Sigils: Familiar, Dust Power, Heart of Dust
Flavor Text: Hardly stands on its own.
A lowly hermit gleaning from scraps.
The corpses it makes fuel it with power.
Powerful magick in a fleeting form.
The might of the jungle has awoken.
They'll knock the magick out of you.

Tribes: Wizard Wizard Wizard Wizard Wizard Wizard
Flavor Text: A self similar magick, honed to infinity.
All things good must end...
It feasts on broken relics.
Frail, but powerful beyond belief.
The all-consuming terror from the abyss.
Their greatest work, themselves.
Their servants are lucky to have them.
"Uhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh..."
"AARRGH! I'll try my best!"
This attack could have been predicted.
A rebel among the ranks.
Still practices with healing crystals.
king gizzard died in the bite of 87
Ever stalwart in the face of challenge.
With practice, even mox have potential.
Good for getting hit, but not much else.
An expert jeweler.
A hulking construct driven by mox.
Some mox magicks can be very unstable.
Summoned when a formation is broken.
Without form, but charged in its will.
Stopping awry magicks is quite a feat.
The price of insubordinance is pain.
The magic of beasts, the beast of magic.
Protective of what fuels their magic.
A mox gained form... how curious.
Don't look it in the eyes. It'll go away.
A proud mage's honor never dies.
Rallying the inanimate into a fervour.
No longer suited to live in the wild.
An imprenetrable defense, when empowered.

Sigils: Gem Animator, Gem Instability, Gem Greed
Flavor Text: A paragon of gem augmentation.
Sworn to protect, for all eternity.
Hungry for riches and power.
"Ideally, you will play me well."
"Doesn't matter!! I got another one!!!"
His success comes from copying others.
Creation is a powerful tool.
It might have found something magical.
Never content with casting a spell once.
Ravenous, driven mad by the gems.
Flight is challenging, but useful.
An intricate construct, driven by mox.
It has learned the summoner's ways.
Nothing spectacular, but entertaining.
Knowledge is power.
Can see the future, but not change it.
Only the fates know what will emerge.
Armed with perfect knowledge of its foe.
Do you wish to know your fate?
A purveyor of dark-market crystals.
He sees magicks as crucial for triumph.
A deadly master of sleight of hand.
Flawless crimes lead to opportunities.
A lust for gems and for blood.
Repelling the greatest of assaults.
Rambles on incorrect spell recitations.
Adept, but troublesome to keep contained.

Sigils: Snag, Purist, RAINBOW, Touch of Death

Flavor Text: Fate has been subdued to their will.

Sigils: Reaction Replica, Double Death, Arcane Echo
Flavor Text: An unmatched master in time.
A wondrous friend to all frog kind.
Aeons, spent learning the mystifying...
"YES! PLAY ME! STIMULATE ME!"
"So... a little help?"
A very loyal magickal companion.
A hybrid, loyal and fierce to a fault.
The utmost dedication to duty.
The frenzy of a newfound might.
Browse his wares for oddities.
All succumb to transformation's chaos.
Revealed secrets are theirs to keep.
Created by Goranj to strengthen them.
Created by Orlu to focus her will.
Created by Bleene to harness his insight.
Admittedly, more brute than wizard.
Fight or flight? Why, both are ideal.
Creation's master, a life for a life.

Sigils: Magnificent Gem, Made of Stone, Death Sentence
Flavor Text: A conduit for truly grand magicks.

Sigils: Gem Detonator, Gem Greed, Energy Gun
Flavor Text: They love casting spells.
"Ierth, fira and aer, all thal I'll need."
"Hah! These new friends are wonderful!"
"Let what you hold dear be scorched."
"Come, my dear! Be yourself here!"
Reinforced with the might of the body.
Made with the dedication of the soul.
Perfected with the ingenuity of the mind.
What is drive without rest?
What is wisdom without discovery?
What is perfection without refinement?
Led astray by falsities and sacrifices.
Power comes from the name you chose.
Twelve sets in the morning, two at eve.
Even mages see the value of energy.
Some souls never find salvation.
No functionality has been inserted.
